                "commentary": "The problem is that after 14...h6 15 Be3 (15 Bh4 g5 16 Bg3 Nf6 is also good for Black) 15...Nf6 White would be in trouble if he allowed ...Nxd5. That means he has to go in for 16 Bb3 Nxe4 17 Rc7 Be6 18 Bxe6 Rxe6 19 Rxb7 Ra6 20 a3 Nd6! when Black has an edge because he has a mobile central pawn majority and White has still not completed his development. This position was reached in Teschner-Fischer, Stockholm IZ 1962. The young Bobby failed to win but other players have since registered the full point in this ending."
