                "commentary": "This is considered to be the most flexible response. Black plans to play ...Na6-c5 and doesn't want to be immediately kicked away by White playing b2-b4. NOTE: The idea of playing ...a5 to secure the c5-square for a black knight is seen throughout the book. This is one of Black's key strategical ideas in the King's Indian."
